<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="B" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Belief" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Belief,</orth> 1) credit given: <bibl n="shak. wiv 5.5.132" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. V, 5, 132</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 5.2.63" default="NO" valid="yes">As V, 2, 63</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 3.1.31" default="NO" valid="yes">John III, 1, 31</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mac 1.3.74" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. I, 3, 74</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mac 4.3.184" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 3, 184</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 1.1.24" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. I, 1, 24</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 3.7.76" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. III, 7, 76</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. per 4.4.23" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. IV, 4, 23</bibl>. <cit><quote>to be in the b.</quote> <bibl n="shak. tn 3.4.149" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. III, 4, 149</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>b. of it,</quote> <bibl n="shak. oth 1.1.144" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. I, 1, 144</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>his b. in her renown,</quote> <bibl n="shak. cym 5.5.202" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. V, 5, 202</bibl></cit>.<lb />2) opinion: <cit><quote>holds b. that, being brought into the open air, it would allay . . . .,</quote> <bibl n="shak. jn 5.7.6" default="NO" valid="yes">John V, 7, 6</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>she's in a wrong b.</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h6 2.3.31" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A II, 3, 31</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>if this but answer to my just b.</quote> <bibl n="shak. per 5.1.239" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. V, 1, 239</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>